#Sampling done already in md amber
#Select solute + first solvation shell for Gaussian QM/MM
#
#Uses cpptraj 'closest' command to retain the N water molecules nearest to
#the solute (residue 1) for each frame.  N=30 covers the first solvation
#shell for a small molecule (~14 atoms) with comfortable margin; reduce to
#20 if you want a tighter shell or increase to 50 for a larger solute.
#The resulting XYZ will have solute atoms first, then the retained waters.
#water_mode in sim.txt controls what happens to those waters in Gaussian.

#inputs
parm ${name}.parm7
trajin ${name}_md.mdcrd 1 last 10

#Re-image so the solute is whole and centred before distance selection
autoimage

#Keep the 30 water molecules closest to residue 1 (the solute).
#'oxygen' keyword tells cpptraj to measure distance to water O atoms.
#'closestout' writes a summary but we don't need it - /dev/null it.
closest 30 :1 oxygen closestout /dev/null

#Re-centre on the solute after selecting the shell
center :1 mass origin
image origin center

trajout ${name}_frame.xyz xyz ftype namexyz multi
run